-- CIT quarterly profit rises
-- 
-- Wed Apr 18, 2007 6:31am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/18/us-cit-results-idUSWNAS661020070418

 

 (Reuters) - CIT Group Inc., ( CIT.N ), a consumer and commercial finance company, said on Wednesday quarterly earnings rose, helped by an increase in new business volume. 

 The company said first quarter profit rose to $271.4 million, or $1.37 a share, from $229.7 million, or $1.12 a share a year earlier. Excluding certain items, the company posted earnings of $1.30 a share, up from $1.13 in the year-ago period. Analysts on average expected earnings of $1.27 a share, before special items, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by Amitha Rajan in Bangalore)